# ============================================================================
# PoCW-WEB Frontend Environment Template
# ============================================================================
# This file is a template only. Copy values into one of these real env files:
# - .env.local      -> local development (next dev)
# - .env.production -> production/testnet/mainnet builds on VPS/CI
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - Frontend variables MUST be prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ to be available
#   in browser code.
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_ values are public by design. Never place private keys/secrets
#   in this frontend env.
# - Oracle private keys and API secrets belong in the oracle-service env only.
# ============================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Oracle API URL
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL:
#   Use your local oracle service URL, e.g. http://localhost:3000
# TESTNET/MAINNET:
#   Use your public HTTPS oracle domain, e.g. https://oracle.yourdomain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_ORACLE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2) Contract addresses by chainId (frontend auto-selects by connected wallet)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The app reads:
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTROLLER_ADDRESS_<chainId>
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_SBT_ADDRESS_<chainId>
#
# When user wallet is on chain 31337, it uses *_31337.
# When user wallet is on chain 84532, it uses *_84532.
#
# You can keep multiple chain configs in one file.
# Wallet network decides which pair is used at runtime.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL HARDHAT (chainId: 31337)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Typical from: npx hardhat node + local deploy
# Safe for dev only.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTROLLER_ADDRESS_31337=0xe7f1725E7734CE288F8367e1Bb143E90bb3F0512
NEXT_PUBLIC_SBT_ADDRESS_31337=0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BASE SEPOLIA TESTNET (chainId: 84532)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Fill these with addresses from your testnet deployment output.
# Example deployment command (contracts repo):
#   npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.ts --network base-sepolia
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTROLLER_ADDRESS_84532=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000
NEXT_PUBLIC_SBT_ADDRESS_84532=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BASE MAINNET (chainId: 8453) - optional template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment and set only after mainnet deployment is complete.
# NOTE: frontend code must support 8453 in src/lib/contracts.ts.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CONTROLLER_ADDRESS_8453=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SBT_ADDRESS_8453=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3) Recommended file usage by environment
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL DEV (next dev):
#   Put local values in .env.local
# TESTNET STAGING (next build/start on VPS):
#   Put testnet values in .env.production before building
# MAINNET PROD (next build/start on VPS):
#   Put mainnet values in .env.production before building
#
# Because Next.js inlines NEXT_PUBLIC_ values at build time,
# always rebuild frontend after changing these values.


 